---
title: Roasted Garlic & Zucchini Flatbreads with White Sauce, Mozzarella & Grape Tomatoes
description: Move over, marinara—there’s a new sauce in town. In this recipe, crispy flatbreads are slathered with a rich, creamy white sauce we just can’t get enough of. We top it off with melty mozzarella and roasted garlic, plus tender zucchini and juicy marinated tomatoes. Sprinkle with chives and chili flakes if you like a little zip, then sit back and enjoy. Pizza night just got a major upgrade.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/61d4c669ad4ac6524f2a09e1-81e9173e.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/roasted-garlic-zucchini-flatbreads-61d4c669ad4ac6524f2a09e1-5e2b9cad.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/roasted-garlic-and-zucchini-flatbreads-61d4c669ad4ac6524f2a09e1
servings: 2
course: main course
time required: 40 minutes
cuisine: Italian
nutrition:
  calories: 610 kcal
  fat: 32 g
  saturated fat: 15 g
  carbohydrates: 69 g
  sugar: 9 g
  protein: 19 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 870 mg
author: Michelle Doll Olson
---

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat
oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and halve @zucchini{1%unit} lengthwise; slice crosswise into
½-inch-thick half-moons. Peel @garlic{1%clove} and place in the center of a
small piece of #foil{}; drizzle with @olive oil{} and season with @salt{}
and @pepper{}. Cinch into a packet. Halve @grape tomatoes{4%ounce}. Mince
@chives{¼%ounce}.

Toss zucchini on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{}, @Italian
seasoning{1%tsp} (2 tsp for 4 servings), salt, and pepper. Place garlic foil
packet on same #sheet{}.

Roast on top rack, tossing halfway through, until zucchini is browned and
tender, ~{14-16%minutes}.

Meanwhile, place tomatoes in a #medium bowl{}; toss with a drizzle of olive
oil, @Italian seasoning{1%tsp} (2 tsp for 4), salt, and pepper. (You'll use
the remaining Italian seasoning later.) Set aside to marinate.

Once zucchini is tender, transfer to #bowl{} with tomatoes; toss to combine.

Leaving garlic foil packet on sheet, carefully wipe off any excess oil.
Place @flatbreads{2%units} on same sheet. (For 4 servings, divide between 2
sheets; toast on top and middle racks, swapping rack positions halfway through
toasting.)

Return to top rack until flatbreads are lightly toasted and garlic is softened,
~{5-7%minutes}.

While flatbreads toast, melt @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in a
#large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @flour{1%tablespoon}, @garlic powder{1%tsp},
and remaining @Italian seasoning{1%tsp}. Whisk constantly until lightly browned,
~{30%seconds}.

Reduce heat to medium low and whisk in @cream cheese{4%tablespoon} and
@water{½%cup} (1 cup for 4) until melted and combined. Season generously with
salt and pepper. Simmer until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove pan from heat.

Once garlic is done, carefully transfer to a #cutting board{} and roughly chop.

Heat broiler to high.

Evenly top flatbreads with sauce, roasted garlic, and veggies. Sprinkle with
@mozzarella cheese{½%cup}.

Broil flatbreads until cheese melts, ~{1-2%minutes}. (For 4 servings, broil in
batches.)

> TIP: Watch carefully to avoid burning.

Slice flatbreads into pieces; sprinkle with chives and @chili flakes{1%tsp} to
taste. Divide between plates and serve.